author: rooneg
msg: If a test exits due to a signal, then show the signal number.  If the
test exits with a non-0 value, show the value.  This only has effect
in verbose mode and on platforms that return status values.
Patch by: Dan Christian <dchristian@google.com>
* subversion/tests/cmdline/svntest/main.py
(spawn_process):  Fix exit code handling and add messages.

author: xsteve
msg: Use " *svn-process*" instead of "*svn-process*" as process buffer name
Patch by "Aaron Hawley" <aaron.s.hawley@gmail.com>
* trunk/contrib/client-side/emacs/psvn.el:
(svn-process-buffer-name): Set a new default value. This way the
*svn-process* buffer does not clutter the buffer list
(svn-prepare-bug-report): Use svn-process-buffer-name
